@node "Intr" "Introduction"
I once saw a door on a MAXs  board  that  let  you  talk  to  the
sysop.  Of course, it wasn't the fecking sysop at all, and I left
crying. So, here is a version of  that  for  AmiExpress.  A  fake
pager  door is first activated, followed by the sysop breaking in
for a natter - via a fake chat.
@endnode
@node "spec" "Specifications"
Mo-Email is currently running on my:  A1200/020/882
                                      10 Meg RAM
                                      85 Meg Drive
                                      /X version 4.#?
@endnode
@node "Impo" "Important!"
Basically  it's  as  clever as your .DAT files, some of which are
supplied. It will read a  user's input  and  respond  accordingly
(well,  in  a  simple  pattern-matching  way).  It  will give the
appearance of the sysop typing via  the  RAND/DELAY  commands  in
Arexx.  A  different delay value between each character appearing
on screen etc. This can be adjusted.

All    entered  text  from  the  sysop/victim  is  saved  into  a
time-stamped text file for later public humiliation.

As usual, Mo-products are  public  domain.  I  don't  believe  in
shareware.  Emailware  is  cool though, as I would like to read a
few Mo-Intelligence saved-responses:)
@endnode
