@node "inst" "Getting this sod to work..."
(1) Copy all files to where they should  be,  renaming  the  main
command  icon if necessary. Cool people will rename it to 'o' and
replace their existing pager, which will be renamed to  something
non-lamers will know.

(2)  Go  through  the 'die.rexx' text and look for comments. This
will allow you to change the speed at which the sysop types,  how
many lines he will type before leaving etc.

(3) Ermmmmm...:)


(4) Libraries needed:
    rexxtricks.library   - here
    rexxsyslib.library
    rexxsupport.library  - here

Most important!
Main  rule:  When  editing the '#?.DAT' or '.cfg' files make SURE
there are NO blank lines in the file when saved, else  this  will
screw up responses for the user.

Basically, you can add your own responses to keywords.

The main file is 'words.cfg':

 hello   greeting.dat
 hiya    greeting.dat
 sunny   weather.dat
 rain    weather.dat

Each line of this cfg file must contain only two words.

(1) Keyword          (2) File to read from (no full path names)

Play around and you'll get the idea.

A user's input is interpreted as follows: The  script  takes  his
sentence  and  does  a 'matchpattern' routine for keywords in the
'words.cfg' file. If he/she(?) types:

'Hello to you sysop'

The script will probably find  '#?hello#?'  and  respond  with  a
line from the 'greeting.dat' file.
@endnode
