@endnode
@node "Bugs" "Those feckin crawlies..."
Sometimes  keywords and their matching filenames fail to give the
correct response. Try  changing  their  order  in  the  words.cfg
list.  It  may work. Not a problem. This whole door is just a bit
of fun and not to be taken seriously. Damn it.

Note: The following doesn't always work. Might work once  in  any
      given line of text. Unknown why.

You can give the appearance of the sysop making a typo  by  using
Ansi  Control  Char:  *[1D  - where '*' is the escape code thang.
You know, it looks like  a  little  box.  Get  this  by  pressing
LEFTAMIGA+ESCAPE  - which usually exits the editor program you're
running because they never gave this any thought, damn it. Hehe.

So, the following will type 'sabfra'...
...then 'delete' the 'b' and turn it into 'safra':

sab*[1Dfra
@endnode
